@startuml
title Dining Philosophers Program Flow

start
:`DiningTable.main()` creates a `DiningTable`
with 5 philosophers and 3 meals each;

:Normalize inputs;
:Create `Chopstick[]`;
:Create `Philosopher[]`;
:Create one `Thread` per philosopher;

:`startDinner()`;
:Start all philosopher threads;

fork
  group Philosopher Thread (`Philosopher.run()`)
    repeat
      :Set state to `PHILOSOPHIZING`;
      :Print philosophizing message;
      :Pause for a random time;

      :Set state to `HUNGRY`;
      :Choose lower-numbered chopstick first;

      :`first.pickUp(this)`;
      if (First chopstick owned?) then (yes)
        :Wait until notified;
      endif

      :`second.pickUp(this)`;
      if (Second chopstick owned?) then (yes)
        :Wait until notified;
      endif

      :Set state to `EATING`;
      :Print eating message;
      :Pause for a random time;

      :`second.putDown(this)`;
      :Notify waiting philosophers;
      :`first.putDown(this)`;
      :Notify waiting philosophers;
    repeat while (More meals remain?) is (yes)

    :Print leaving-table message;
    :Thread wrapper calls
    `DiningTable.philosopherFinished()`;
  end group
fork again
  :Other philosopher threads
  run the same loop concurrently;
end fork

:Increment completed philosopher count;
if (All philosopher threads finished?) then (yes)
  :`notifyAll()` waiting table thread;
else (no)
  :`notify()` waiting table thread;
endif

:`startDinner()` stops waiting;
stop

note right
Deadlock is avoided because each philosopher
always acquires the lower-numbered chopstick first,
which removes circular wait.
end note

@enduml
